5
1 (s) The executive director of the Indiana education savings authority
2 shall submit or cause to be submitted to the department a copy of all
3 information returns or statements issued to account owners, account
4 beneficiaries, and other taxpayers for each taxable year with respect to:
5 (1) nonqualified withdrawals made from accounts, including
6 subaccounts of an Indiana529 plan for the taxable year; or
7 (2) account closings for the taxable year.
8 (t) The following apply to contributions made after December 31,
9 2023:
10 (1) For purposes of this section, all or part of a contribution made
11 after the end of a taxable year, and not later than the due date of
12 the taxpayer's adjusted gross income tax return for the taxable
13 year under this article (as determined without regard to any
14 allowable extensions), shall be considered as having been made
15 during the taxable year preceding the contribution if:
16 (A) the taxpayer elects to treat all or part of a contribution as
17 occurring in the taxable year preceding the contribution;
18 (B) the taxpayer designates the amounts of the contribution to
19 be treated as occurring in each taxable year, in the case of a
20 single contribution that is to be allowable under this section in
21 two (2) separate years; and
22 (C) the taxpayer irrevocably waives the right to claim the
23 contribution claimed in the taxable year preceding the
24 contribution as occurring in the taxable year of the
25 contribution.
26 (2) The Indiana education savings authority may prescribe any
27 forms necessary for purposes of this subsection.
28 SECTION 2. An emergency is declared for this act.
